#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:12
msgid "Information about the Data and Privacy"
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:18
msgid "Plugin Authorization Flow (OAuth)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:21
msgid "For technical reasons, a short-lived authorization code generated by the OAuth flow is sent from your browser to our server as part of the authentication process. This code allows the plugin to access the Google Drive API on your behalf."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:25
msgid "The plugin obtains the following information when you use the built-in app for authentication:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:29
msgid "Your WordPress website URL."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:30
msgid "A short-lived OAuth authorization code."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:45
msgid "On your server, the authorization code is exchanged for an access token and a refresh token, which are securely encrypted and stored locally. The authorization code can only be used once and expires immediately after exchange or within minutes if unused."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:51
msgid "Important:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:51
msgid "After authorization, all communication occurs directly between your server and the cloud storage service servers. This communication is encrypted and does not pass through our servers. We do not collect, store, or have access to your files."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:59
msgid "Google Permissions for OAuth"
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:62
msgid "To ensure seamless functionality, users grant Google Drive permissions during the standard OAuth authorization process. For more information, please refer to Google’s privacy policies."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:76
msgid "View permission allows the plugin to list your files."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:77
msgid "Create permission enables uploading new content to your Google Drive."
msgstr ""

#: includes/views/getting-started/data-privacy.php:78
msgid "Additional permissions allow renaming, editing, deleting, and sharing your files."
msgstr ""

